1
00:00:08,810 --> 00:00:10,810


2
00:00:10,810 --> 00:00:12,740
You guys listen up!

3
00:00:12,760 --> 00:00:15,350
This person sitting behind me!

4
00:00:15,780 --> 00:00:17,710
He's the new 3rd Squad Captain!

5
00:00:17,740 --> 00:00:19,630
Tetta Kisaki!

6
00:00:25,570 --> 00:00:27,690
Hey, hey, what is going on?

7
00:00:28,750 --> 00:00:31,080
Looks like this is getting interesting.

8
00:00:36,770 --> 00:00:38,320
What are you doing here, Baji?

9
00:00:38,820 --> 00:00:41,810
You've been banned from our
gatherings for causing that infight.

10
00:00:42,120 --> 00:00:45,870
Since I ruined your precious gathering,

11
00:00:45,920 --> 00:00:47,730
will you finally kick me out this time?

12
00:00:48,340 --> 00:00:51,100
What? What is this guy talking about?

13
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:54,690
You don't need troublemaker, right?

14
00:00:54,720 --> 00:00:55,720
Mikey.

15
00:00:56,360 --> 00:00:57,560
Baji!

16
00:00:58,950 --> 00:01:00,320
I quit.

17
00:01:01,120 --> 00:01:04,459
From now on, Keisuke Baji,
the 1st Squad Captain...

18
00:01:04,959 --> 00:01:07,720
...will be Toman's enemy!

19
00:01:11,200 --> 00:01:13,780
I have a favor for you, Takemicchi.

20
00:01:15,289 --> 00:01:16,289
Yes.

21
00:01:16,640 --> 00:01:19,010
Bring Baji back from Valhalla for me.

22
00:01:20,150 --> 00:01:21,670
Can you do that for me?

23
00:01:22,720 --> 00:01:23,890
Yes!

24
00:01:23,910 --> 00:01:26,060
If it's for you, of course!

25
00:01:26,420 --> 00:01:27,690
But...

26
00:01:27,970 --> 00:01:31,910
Can I also ask just one thing from you?

27
00:01:33,270 --> 00:01:34,270
Kisaki...

28
00:01:35,240 --> 00:01:37,380
Please expel him from Toman.

29
00:01:38,070 --> 00:01:39,350
Okay.

30
00:01:40,009 --> 00:01:42,229
We will clash with Valhalla soon enough.

31
00:01:42,810 --> 00:01:45,210
Your job is to get Baji back before then.

32
00:01:45,950 --> 00:01:49,430
Prove that you're more useful than Kisaki.

33
00:02:34,130 --> 00:02:35,170
Let's hurry!

34
00:02:35,190 --> 00:02:36,910
Hey, don't run in the hallway!

35
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:53,310
Bring Baji back from Valhalla for me.

36
00:02:53,910 --> 00:02:55,280
And if you fail...

37
00:02:56,030 --> 00:02:57,340
I'll kill you.

38
00:02:58,320 --> 00:03:00,000
What should I do?

39
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:01,740
Takemichi!

40
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,260
We heard the news.

41
00:03:04,290 --> 00:03:06,940
So you became a member of Toman?

42
00:03:07,300 --> 00:03:08,530
Akkun...

43
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,960
Hm? What's wrong?

44
00:03:13,990 --> 00:03:15,640
You don't look so happy.

45
00:03:15,740 --> 00:03:16,630
Eh?

46
00:03:16,660 --> 00:03:18,370
Ah, th-that's right.

47
00:03:19,350 --> 00:03:21,410
I became a member of Toman.

48
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:22,570
Just turned out that way.

49
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:25,130
Really? So what happened?

50
00:03:25,590 --> 00:03:28,410
I can't look directly at Akkun!

51
00:03:29,460 --> 00:03:32,200
The "Crybaby Takemichi" is now a Toman, huh.

52
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:34,510
Wish we could join, too.

53
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:38,780
It's not as good as you'd think.

54
00:03:44,260 --> 00:03:49,100
We got our collars grabbed
and took an intense punch

55
00:03:49,130 --> 00:03:54,010
After we got beaten up
Together we crouched

56
00:03:54,010 --> 00:03:56,430
The anticipated rain came

57
00:03:56,430 --> 00:04:04,770
“This should clean your bruise”
you lied with a smile

58
00:04:04,770 --> 00:04:12,770
Even though you're
bad at argument

59
00:04:12,770 --> 00:04:17,990
So stop making such lame jokes

60
00:04:17,990 --> 00:04:23,120
It's so bad I teared up

61
00:04:23,120 --> 00:04:30,710
Getting blue bruises all the time
I cry, cry, and cry

62
00:04:30,710 --> 00:04:37,380
Leaning our unstable heart together

63
00:04:37,380 --> 00:04:42,050
We fight against the rotten Bad End

64
00:04:42,050 --> 00:04:43,810
I wonder why

65
00:04:43,810 --> 00:04:51,940
The pleasant pain was more vivid,
even more than the happiness

66
00:04:51,940 --> 00:04:56,570
Clicking our tongue over our wet clothes

67
00:04:56,570 --> 00:04:59,950
We look at each other's faces and laugh

68
00:04:59,950 --> 00:05:12,130
The Revenge we swore in that rainy night

69
00:05:16,230 --> 00:05:17,580
I see.

70
00:05:18,060 --> 00:05:23,400
So unless you get that former 1st Squad
Captain named Baji-kun from Valhalla,

71
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:25,860
Mikey-kun will kill you?

72
00:05:25,990 --> 00:05:26,940
Yeah.

73
00:05:26,970 --> 00:05:30,530
And I only got time until
Toman's fight with Valhalla starts.

74
00:05:30,530 --> 00:05:33,330
But no telling when
will that happen, right?

75
00:05:33,330 --> 00:05:34,659
It can even be today.

76
00:05:34,659 --> 00:05:38,370
May you rest in peace, Takemichi.
I will pick up your bones.

77
00:05:38,690 --> 00:05:43,330
To be honest, I don't know anything
about the situation inside Toman.

78
00:05:43,659 --> 00:05:46,420
Much less anything about Valhalla.

79
00:05:46,700 --> 00:05:48,300
Hey, Gang Dex.

80
00:05:48,540 --> 00:05:49,360
Huh?

81
00:05:49,380 --> 00:05:51,470
Well, if you insist.

82
00:05:51,490 --> 00:05:53,320
Let me explain!

83
00:05:55,909 --> 00:05:59,020
Tokyo Manji Gang, Toman for short.

84
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:02,640
Mikey-kun is the President
and Draken-kun is the Vice-President.

85
00:06:02,670 --> 00:06:04,550
Under them are five squads.

86
00:06:04,580 --> 00:06:07,340
Each squad has around 20 guys each.

87
00:06:07,750 --> 00:06:10,760
They're a large Bosozoku
with 100 members total.

88
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:13,790
You know this much, right?

89
00:06:13,810 --> 00:06:15,920
Wow. I didn't know that.

90
00:06:15,950 --> 00:06:19,330
For real?
And you call yourself a delinquent?

91
00:06:19,430 --> 00:06:20,430
Sorry.

92
00:06:20,450 --> 00:06:23,510
Make sure you take a note.
This will be on the exam!

93
00:06:24,850 --> 00:06:26,510
There! No chitchat!

94
00:06:26,510 --> 00:06:28,090
He's totally on the role.

95
00:06:29,740 --> 00:06:31,640
From what I've heard.

96
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:35,170
The former 3rd Squad Captain,
Pah-chin-kun got arrested.

97
00:06:35,500 --> 00:06:38,810
And the Vice-Captain, Peh-yan-kun,
joined the 2nd Squad.

98
00:06:39,130 --> 00:06:43,030
Eh? So Peh-yan-kun is
under Mitsuya-kun now?

99
00:06:43,190 --> 00:06:44,230
Yeah.

100
00:06:44,250 --> 00:06:46,270
We're in the same squad?!

101
00:06:46,300 --> 00:06:48,520
I can't really handle being with him.

102
00:06:48,659 --> 00:06:49,890
Takemicchi!

103
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:51,170
His voice scares me.

104
00:06:51,460 --> 00:06:55,380
And, in exchange,
the new 3rd Squad Captain is...

105
00:06:56,270 --> 00:06:57,370
Kisaki!

106
00:06:57,800 --> 00:07:00,190
Yes! The former Moebius member.

107
00:07:00,690 --> 00:07:03,980
Moebius wasn't exactly one
solid group to begin with.

108
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:07,290
Apparently, there was tension between
Osanai's group, those born in 1998

109
00:07:07,310 --> 00:07:11,160
and Kisaki's group, those born in 1990.

110
00:07:11,590 --> 00:07:13,290
Hmm, I see.

111
00:07:13,520 --> 00:07:15,890
I suppose a gang got
a lot going on inside them.

112
00:07:15,890 --> 00:07:20,360
After Osanai lost to Mikey-kun,
Moebius is essentially disbanded.

113
00:07:20,760 --> 00:07:24,730
Then, the 1990 group led
by Kisaki joined Toman.

114
00:07:24,760 --> 00:07:29,050
Making Toman's numbers
jump from 100 to 150.

115
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:35,020
That makes Kisaki's 3rd Squad
way bigger than any others in Toman.

116
00:07:35,810 --> 00:07:39,580
Toman needs Kisaki's strength
to move forward.

117
00:07:41,750 --> 00:07:45,770
What about the 1988 group
who was with Osanai?

118
00:07:46,920 --> 00:07:50,390
The remaining 88' and 89'
have gathered...

119
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:52,280
Under Shuji Hanma.

120
00:07:53,110 --> 00:07:54,550
That guy?

121
00:07:57,290 --> 00:08:02,210
He did say he was Moebius's temporary
president during the battle of 8/3.

122
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:04,510
And Hanma gathered ex-Moebius members

123
00:08:04,530 --> 00:08:08,220
along with anti-Toman force
to make a new gang named...

124
00:08:08,610 --> 00:08:10,070
Valhalla.

125
00:08:10,070 --> 00:08:12,970
Valhalla currently has 300 members!

126
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:15,230
300 members...

127
00:08:15,840 --> 00:08:18,160
And Hanma is Valhalla's leader?

128
00:08:20,490 --> 00:08:22,640
Hanma is the "acting president."

129
00:08:22,670 --> 00:08:24,950
No one knows the real president.

130
00:08:25,130 --> 00:08:27,370
The "face" of the President does not exist.

131
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:32,799
That's why people call Valhalla
as "The Headless Angel."

132
00:08:32,799 --> 00:08:35,799
And Baji-kun joined that kind of gang?

133
00:08:35,799 --> 00:08:38,470
To bring Baji-kun back to Toman.

134
00:08:38,470 --> 00:08:41,330
I've got no choice but to
meet him in person.

135
00:08:41,890 --> 00:08:44,010
But how?

136
00:08:45,050 --> 00:08:46,050
Done.

137
00:08:46,490 --> 00:08:47,730
Hey, you two.

138
00:08:48,100 --> 00:08:50,820
Do you know what class
the 2nd-year Hanagaki is in?

139
00:08:50,820 --> 00:08:52,940
-Eh?
-He is in class 3.

140
00:08:52,940 --> 00:08:54,400
Hmm...

141
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:55,720
Thank you.

142
00:09:00,620 --> 00:09:03,080
Since when we have such
a hottie in our school?

143
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:05,460
Going by his school shoe color,
he's a 3rd-year, right?

144
00:09:06,540 --> 00:09:10,340
The ex-Moebius member are
under Hanma, Valhalla's No.2.

145
00:09:10,340 --> 00:09:13,510
And the anti-Toman forced are under...

146
00:09:17,470 --> 00:09:20,320
The No.3, Kazutora Hanemiya.

147
00:09:28,810 --> 00:09:29,880
Eh?

148
00:09:40,330 --> 00:09:43,330
Is school over already?

149
00:09:43,330 --> 00:09:46,650
Who the hell are you?
You don't look familiar.

150
00:09:46,870 --> 00:09:49,080
That's not very polite.

151
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:51,380
I'm actually your senior in this school.

152
00:09:51,380 --> 00:09:54,660
Huh? Who are you?
Never seen you before.

153
00:10:00,890 --> 00:10:03,090
That tiger tattoo on his neck!

154
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:04,840
Stop it, Makoto! This guy is...!

155
00:10:04,860 --> 00:10:06,630
Huh? What is it?

156
00:10:07,060 --> 00:10:10,270
Hey, you guys know Takemichi Hanagaki?

157
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:12,680
T-Takemichi...

158
00:10:12,710 --> 00:10:14,080
That's him.

159
00:10:14,420 --> 00:10:15,420
Huh?

160
00:10:15,590 --> 00:10:16,950
Takemichi?

161
00:10:16,980 --> 00:10:20,670
Th-This guy here is Valhalla's No.3!

162
00:10:20,870 --> 00:10:22,370
Kazutora Hanemiya!

163
00:10:22,410 --> 00:10:25,200
(Valhalla No.3 - Kazutora Hanemiya)

164
00:10:29,190 --> 00:10:30,850
I'm so happy!

165
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:33,910
I had no idea there was someone
in Toman one grade below mine!

166
00:10:34,450 --> 00:10:35,790
Okay, Takemichi!

167
00:10:35,810 --> 00:10:37,820
-Eh?
-Let's go to Valhalla's hideout.

168
00:10:37,850 --> 00:10:39,380
Huh? Valhalla?!

169
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:42,060
Hey! I found Takemichi!

170
00:10:42,560 --> 00:10:43,560
Huh?

171
00:10:43,590 --> 00:10:45,040
So that's the guy?

172
00:10:45,060 --> 00:10:46,090
Yub.

173
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:48,310
Wh-Who are these guys?

174
00:10:48,450 --> 00:10:51,660
Hmm? My most trusted junior.

175
00:10:52,160 --> 00:10:54,200
I-I see...

176
00:10:54,280 --> 00:10:55,880
Did anything happen?

177
00:10:55,980 --> 00:10:57,530
They both on crutches...

178
00:10:57,820 --> 00:10:59,800
Huh? I broke 'em yesterday.

179
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:00,960
Eh?!

180
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:03,910
But they're your most
trusted juniors, right?

181
00:11:03,910 --> 00:11:04,930
Yeah.

182
00:11:04,960 --> 00:11:07,330
You got a problem with Kazutora-kun?

183
00:11:07,330 --> 00:11:08,410
No...

184
00:11:10,110 --> 00:11:14,420
How can they be so calm
about having their legs broken?

185
00:11:14,740 --> 00:11:17,590
In any case, this guy is
definitely a bad news!

186
00:11:18,220 --> 00:11:20,280
Hurry up, Takemichi!

187
00:11:20,310 --> 00:11:23,700
Valhalla's No.3, Kazutora Hanemiya.

188
00:11:24,310 --> 00:11:26,980
Isn't it a bad idea to go
along with this guy?

189
00:11:27,250 --> 00:11:28,740
We're going to the enemy's hideout!

190
00:11:29,390 --> 00:11:31,160
Just relax!

191
00:11:31,180 --> 00:11:32,950
I'll introduce you to everyone.

192
00:11:33,230 --> 00:11:34,520
Everyone?

193
00:11:34,520 --> 00:11:37,760
Could this be a chance to meet Baji-kun?!

194
00:11:38,740 --> 00:11:41,570
But... I'm kinda scared.

195
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:53,390
Do you want to go to that
store I talked about before?

196
00:11:53,450 --> 00:11:54,850
Yeah, let's go!

197
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:56,960
-I wonder what to eat today.
-Let's see...

198
00:11:57,100 --> 00:11:57,950
Hina...

199
00:11:57,980 --> 00:11:58,910
I want to eat perfait!

200
00:11:58,940 --> 00:12:00,000
Sounds good!

201
00:12:02,220 --> 00:12:04,230
I promised back then.

202
00:12:05,150 --> 00:12:07,810
That I'll do anything to protect you.

203
00:12:09,640 --> 00:12:11,280
Valhalla's hideout.

204
00:12:13,450 --> 00:12:14,950
Bring it on!

205
00:12:16,140 --> 00:12:18,690
If I can bring Baji-kun back to Toman,

206
00:12:18,690 --> 00:12:22,450
Mikey-kun promised me that
he will expel Kisaki.

207
00:12:22,450 --> 00:12:25,240
As long as I can get
Kisaki out of Toman...

208
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:27,240
The future will change!

209
00:12:28,510 --> 00:12:31,930
I won't let that future
happen ever again!

210
00:12:33,340 --> 00:12:34,520
Watch me!

211
00:12:35,090 --> 00:12:36,160
Hina!

212
00:12:53,300 --> 00:12:55,590
Who lets you walk around here?

213
00:12:56,440 --> 00:12:57,860
Um...

214
00:12:57,860 --> 00:12:59,390
Hanemiya-kun.

215
00:12:59,420 --> 00:13:00,340
Hmm?

216
00:13:00,410 --> 00:13:01,810
Just call me Kazutora.

217
00:13:02,360 --> 00:13:04,010
Kazutora-kun.

218
00:13:04,650 --> 00:13:07,570
You're a third-year at our school, right?

219
00:13:07,570 --> 00:13:08,910
Yeah.

220
00:13:08,910 --> 00:13:10,240
Umm...

221
00:13:10,240 --> 00:13:13,580
I just figured everyone would
make a big deal knowing someone

222
00:13:13,580 --> 00:13:16,250
as famous as you been
in our school all this time.

223
00:13:16,250 --> 00:13:19,540
I only went for one semester as a first-year.

224
00:13:19,540 --> 00:13:20,680
Eh?

225
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:23,130
I've been going to reform school.

226
00:13:23,160 --> 00:13:24,160
Eh?!

227
00:13:27,260 --> 00:13:29,050
Reform school...

228
00:13:29,940 --> 00:13:31,640
You got arrested?

229
00:13:33,470 --> 00:13:34,820
It was his fault.

230
00:13:35,980 --> 00:13:38,040
Look, we're almost there.

231
00:13:38,490 --> 00:13:39,700
His?

232
00:13:39,860 --> 00:13:41,360
Who is he talking about?

233
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:45,670
Anyway, I must sneak into
Valhalla and take Baji-kun back!

234
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:51,020
Eh? In here?

235
00:13:51,410 --> 00:13:52,410
Yub.

236
00:13:52,430 --> 00:13:53,490
The arcade?

237
00:13:54,020 --> 00:13:55,980
Already closed down
a long time ago, though.

238
00:13:56,370 --> 00:13:58,460
(No Trespassing)

239
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:03,860
Headless angel...

240
00:14:22,160 --> 00:14:26,060
The atmosphere here is clearly
different from Toman.

241
00:14:44,840 --> 00:14:45,740
Eh?

242
00:14:46,430 --> 00:14:47,970
Baji-kun?!

243
00:14:49,020 --> 00:14:51,090
Kazutora-kun...

244
00:14:51,090 --> 00:14:53,810
What's going on here?

245
00:14:53,810 --> 00:14:56,460
What do you mean?
It's a loyalty test.

246
00:14:56,490 --> 00:14:57,650
Loyalty test?

247
00:14:58,050 --> 00:15:00,370
We're testing Baji's belief.

248
00:15:01,020 --> 00:15:03,940
If he wants to "switch religion"
from Toman to Valhalla,

249
00:15:03,940 --> 00:15:06,170
he needs to show he's truly ready for it.

250
00:15:06,980 --> 00:15:11,070
The guy Baji is punching right now
is Toman's 1st Squad Vice-Captain.

251
00:15:11,070 --> 00:15:13,570
Baji's most trusted retainer.

252
00:15:13,570 --> 00:15:15,620
1st Squad Vice-Captain?!

253
00:15:15,620 --> 00:15:18,160
Toman is Valhalla's enemy.

254
00:15:19,800 --> 00:15:24,610
If he's betraying his old "God," Mikey
then he needs to stomp his old beliefs.

255
00:15:36,400 --> 00:15:37,650
Well?

256
00:15:37,870 --> 00:15:40,670
Is this good enough for you, Hanma-kun?

257
00:15:41,360 --> 00:15:43,130
For my initiation into Valhalla.

258
00:15:47,190 --> 00:15:49,110
(Sin & Punishment)

259
00:15:53,410 --> 00:15:55,120
You sure are something.

260
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:57,430
He was with you for a long time, right?

261
00:15:57,920 --> 00:16:00,410
I'm impressed you can go that far.

262
00:16:03,010 --> 00:16:04,140
What?

263
00:16:04,330 --> 00:16:06,600
I didn't come here to
listen to some dumb lectures.

264
00:16:09,520 --> 00:16:11,110
Kazutora.

265
00:16:11,290 --> 00:16:12,500
Yeah?

266
00:16:13,850 --> 00:16:15,570
Did you get him?

